Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since September 19 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, if for $9,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entere d For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OCTOBER FROST had an ideal trip nestled on the fence behind the front threesome down the back straight, waited patiently in hand on the far turn behind the contesting trio, angled out for clear run in the three path at the furlong marker and got up in the last few strides for the victory. INFAMOUS COVERT prompted three wide on the first turn, kept a close eye tracking the frontrunner down the backstretch, pounced to bid for the lead three wide at the quarter pole and was determinedly battling to the finish, could no match the winner late but gamely held for the place share at the wire. GENDRAGON took command from the start, opened up mildly on the fence down the backside, was headed outside at the quarter pole, stubbornly dueled on the fence through the stretch, rider lost his crop inside the eighth pole driving to the wire and just missed in the photo for place at the finish line. ROCKLAND EXPRESS trailed on the fence in the early going, stalked between foes near the rear at the half, rallied three wide mid-turn picking up horses, swung outside in the five path straightening for home and had an even pace to the wire to settle on the fringes. JMR PURE SENSATION stalked near the back of the pack down the backstretch inside, made little progress on the fence through the final bend, shifted outside in the three path for the drive, angled inwards to the rail at the furlong pole and showed some late interest on the rail in deep stretch. GIANT ONE broke outwards on the start, settled in midfield four wide on the first turn, made little impact three wide with runners on each side on the final turn and passed a couple of weary foes in the stretch. MO TOURIST pressed the pace between rivals into the first turn, tracked the pacesetter down the back straight, was ridden trying to keep pace with the leaders at the three furlong marker, could find no more around the bend and gave way in upper stretch. THUNDERHEAVYRAIN was brushed inside at the start, stalked near the rear down the backside, made an early move going around horses four wide at the three eighths marker, could not sustain the run turning for home and tired in mid-stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: STEAK AND CHEESE took control on the rail from the start, relaxed smartly down the backstretch, was pressed briefly outside at the half, was let out a notch to open up into the turn, extended the advantage smartly around the final turn and cruised home down the stretch. COLEYVILLE co-trailed on the inside at the half, weaved between foes making his run midway on the far turn, rallied up the fence turning for home, stubbornly chased the winner to the finish line and bested the rest easily with another solid effort. DERZKII travelled four wide in midfield on the first turn, tracked in the second flight two wide outside down the back straight, urged three wide on the turn and ran on mildly down the stretch to capture third money in the end. SUNSPEAR had a good spot watching the front duo rating kindly on the fence down the backside, edged closer inside at the half, chased the winner in vain around the far turn and faded late in the final sixteenth for a minor role. KIDDIE HOLIDAY stalked close to the back of the pack in the early going, was scrubbed on but could not close the gap on the leader through the final oval and was one paced down the lane. SOLAR co-trailed on the outside down the back straight, put in a mild run three wide in midturn but could not get involved in the late stages of the race. NATIVE PRINCE stalked near the rear on the fence down the backside, was asked to go on three furlongs out, made little impression running around the far bend and showed little in the stretch run. BET settled in midfield between runners down the backstretch, could not offer a rally throughout the far turn and was not a factor in the drive to the finish line. HULLABALOO tracked the leader in the first turn, turned up the pressure at the half to press the frontrunner outside, quickly was repelled, was roused between foes chasing on the far turn and emptied out in upper stretch.

PAINTED GLORY pressed outside in the first turn, continued to hound the pacesetter outside throughout the far turn, dueled up front bobbing heads for the lead down the stretch and gave way late just being caught for third money at the wire. GOOD NEWS MONEY set the pace on the rail in the first turn, dictated terms with a slim advantage down the backside, dueled gamely inside in upper stretch, but needed more late and faded on the fence nearing the wire. DARE TO BE KING was off slow breaking inwards at the start, travelled near the back having one rival beat at the half mile marker, had to wait behind runners on the fence throughout the final turn and finished with interest having clear run inside in deep stretch. THIS DUDE A BREEZE was squeezed on the break, settled three wide outside in mid-pack, rallied around foes three wide on the final turn loomed in the four path at the top of the lane but had no more run to give at the furlong pole and weakened in deep stretch. WAR IN CHARGE prompted five wide outside on the first turn, forced the issue three deep down the back straight, was scrubbed on for more three wide at the three furlong marker, could not offer a rally and backed away through the field at the quarter pole. GIOVANNINO pressed the pace four wide between in the first turn, tracked the leader on the outside through the backside, edged closer to the leaders in traffic on the far turn, was in the thick of things up front three wide turning for home, had to check losing her path at the sixteenth pole and could not regroup in time. BIG SHOOTER stalked on the outside three deep near the rear, was steadied three wide between horses at the three furlong marker and and had little to show afterwards. ITS JUST MONEY stalked four deep close to the back of the pack with a half mile to run, offered a brief rally four wide around at the three eighths pole but came up empty turning for home five wide.
